1
00:00:01,601 --> 00:00:07,320
If you’re absent-mindedly 
taking the Holy Name,

2
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:10,053
In other words,
you’re just vibrating the sounds

3
00:00:10,243 --> 00:00:13,197
[Back In Focus]

4
00:00:13,879 --> 00:00:17,863
but your mind is elsewhere
 

5
00:00:17,863 --> 00:00:25,073
or thinking of very mundane things,

6
00:00:25,073 --> 00:00:28,853
then he suggests
that it would be better

7
00:00:28,853 --> 00:00:34,910
to do some other type of sevā,

8
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:41,041
and that sevā
will concentrate you.

9
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,334
The necessity of that sevā
will concentrate the mind,

10
00:00:44,334 --> 00:00:48,316
will bring the mind 
back on focus,

11
00:00:48,316 --> 00:00:49,930
and once that’s achieved, then:

12
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:53,187
“sevonmukhe hi jihvādau svayam eva
sphuraty adaḥ” [Brs: 1.2.234];

13
00:00:53,187 --> 00:00:54,895
then we can take the Name.

